The paper discusses popular time series forecasting models, including stochastic models, neural networks, and support vector machines. These models are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses basic issues related to time series analysis, such as stationarity and overfitting, which are important topics in statistics (cs.ST) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents empirical results and performance measures, which are relevant to the field of computational intelligence (cs.SI).
